                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.156/26</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Paraguayan Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gondra</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to my recent notes to
                    you regarding the representations made to this Government by the Construction
                    and Engineering Finance Company of New York, concerning the alleged premature
                    termination of the concession granted to that company by the Paraguayan
                    Government for the improvement of the port and river front at Asuncion. For your
                    further information, I have the honor to inform you that the Department has now
                    received a letter from the Construction and Engineering Finance Company, stating
                    that it has finally made arrangements to secure the necessary funds for carrying
                    out its contract of concession at Asuncion and that these funds will be
                    available as soon as the Paraguayan Government shall have indicated its
                    agreement to the extension of time suggested by this Government in my note to
                    you of February 7, 1919.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
